1 even t license shall not be required to obtain a special event
2 license.
3 D. Charitable auction and charitable alcoholic beverage event
4 license holders may also utilize a licensed caterer to provide
5 additional alcohol services at the event and on the premises.
6 E. The charitable auction license shall authorize the holder
7 thereof to auction wine, spirits and/or beer purchased from a retail
8 package store or received as a gift from an individual if the
9 auction is conducted to raise funds for charitable purposes. The
10 charitable auction license shall be issued for a period not to
11 exceed two (2) days. Only four such licenses shall be issued to an
12 organization in any twelve-month period; provided, institutions of
13 higher education in this state shall not be restricted to the
14 maximum number of auction licenses issued in any twelve-month period
15 pursuant to this subsection. The maximum amount of wine, spirits
16 and/or beer auctioned pursuant to the charitable auction license
17 shall not exceed fifty (50) gallons. All wines, beer and spirits
18 auctioned pursuant to the charitable auction license shall be
19 registered and all fees and taxes shall be paid in accordance with
20 the Oklahoma Alcoholic Beverage Control Act.
21 F. No charitable alcoholic beverage event license shall be
22 required for an organization, association or nonprofit corporation
23 which is an economic development chamber or similar entity, provided
24 the event is not conducted primarily for fundraising purposes, and
